we do. They're called humans.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
There's a concept in space literature called Macrolife. The space colony, with its industries, people, livestock &amp; farm plants, etc, is in effect a living beast. It can move around to get better resources. It can grow &amp; reproduce.<br>
Far more likely than self-replicating reprogrammable nanomachines, space colonies need no new invention to start -no fundamental new discoveries needed to get them going.<br>
 Practise for a few generations in the Solar system before heading out into the cometary halo and interstellar space, but it's all the same, anywhere across the universe once you can eat asteroids &amp; comets.<br>
<br>
